Bankia May Sell 40% Stake in Banco de Valencia, El Mundo Reports

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-09-21T06:41:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/bankia-may-sell-40-stake-in-banco-de-valencia-el-mundo-reports.html
Banco Financiero & de Ahorros SA,
parent company of Bankia SA, wants to divest its 39.3 percent
stake in  Banco de Valencia SA (BVA)  through a sale or other option,  El
Mundo  reported, citing unidentified people close to Bankia.  Bankia, led by Rodrigo Rato, wants a quick solution for its
stake in Banco de Valencia and might consider a sale or takeover
offer for 100 percent of the lender, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  